4ï¸âƒ£ STEP-BY-STEP CRUD OPERATIONS

We will now do each CRUD operation one by one.

ğŸ”¹ STEP 1: CREATE (Insert Data)
Switch to database:
use collegeDB

Insert ONE document:
db.students.insertOne({
  name: "Sreshta",
  roll: 101,
  branch: "CSE"
})

Insert MULTIPLE documents:
db.students.insertMany([
  { name: "Anu", roll: 102, branch: "IT" },
  { name: "Ravi", roll: 103, branch: "ECE" }
])


âœ… CREATE operation completed

ğŸ”¹ STEP 2: READ (Display Data)
Display all records:
db.students.find()

Display specific record:
db.students.find({ roll: 101 })


âœ… READ operation completed

ğŸ”¹ STEP 3: UPDATE (Modify Data)
Update branch of roll number 101:
db.students.updateOne(
  { roll: 101 },
  { $set: { branch: "AI" } }
)

Verify update:
db.students.find({ roll: 101 })


âœ… UPDATE operation completed

ğŸ”¹ STEP 4: DELETE (Remove Data)
Delete one document:
db.students.deleteOne({ roll: 103 })

Verify deletion:
db.students.find()


âœ… DELETE operation completed
